From ROCKNIX (https://github.com/ROCKNIX/abl), GPL-2.0, (c) ROCKNIX contributors.

1. Copy the rocknix_abl folder from the SD card to the root of Android internal storage.

2. Identify the SoC for your device (flashing the wrong ABL can brick the device,
   so match it carefully):

     SM8550 - AYN Odin 2, Odin 2 Mini, Odin 2 Portal, Thor
              AYANEO Pocket EVO, ACE, DMG, DS, S 2K
              Retroid Pocket 6
     SM8650 - AYANEO Pocket S2
              KONKR Pocket FIT (G3 Gen 3)
     SM8750 - AYN Odin 3
              KONKR Pocket FIT (8 Elite)

3. Using "run script as root" in settings, browse to your SoC's folder (e.g.
   rocknix_abl/SM8750) and run backup_abl.sh to back up your current ABL.

4. Copy the backup (abl_a.img and abl_b.img, written into your SoC folder) to your
   PC for safekeeping.

5. Run flash_abl.sh the same way to flash the new ABL.

6. Reboot holding VOL- to enter the ABL menu.

7. In the ABL menu (navigate with VOL-/+, select with POWER):
     - Set your device model
     - Toggle boot mode to Linux
     - Choose Start to exit
